msContents.summary: Incomplete copy of the Gospels, beginning in chapter 44 of Mark and ending in the second chapter of Luke, and notated with divisions for reading on specific days; followed by leaves of a question and answer book about Arabic grammar copied in a different hand. The leaves for this second work have been remargined and inset into larger frames so that the two works could be bound together.

msItem.title: Gospels. Questions and answers about Arabic grammar.

author.name: Free Library of Philadelphia. Rare Book Department. John Frederick Lewis Collection of Oriental Manuscripts

supportDesc.extent: iii, 120, iv leaves : 187 x 120 (111 x 56) mm bound to 185 x 120 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added, top left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 19 long lines; second text written in 12-15 lines; border-ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed. Second work written in naskh with elements of nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrications in red; second text border-ruled in double red.
Description of ms. in pencil in English

binding.p: Rebound in Western style green leather with gold tooled design; horizontal bands on the spine which is stamped "Hindoo Mss."

origin.p: Neither work is dated; possibly 17th or 18th century.
